<TEXT>
premier andreas papandreou has taken the 
greeks by surprise again but this time the focus is on his 
personal life and not his politics 
the 69yearold premier who is awaiting openheart surgery in 
london last week announced he intends to divorce his americanborn 
wife margaret after 37 years of marriage 
the announcement came after papandreou was pictured in greek 
newspapers strolling handinhand through hospital grounds with his 
companion dimitra liani a 34yearold flight attendant 
in a country where politicians private lives usually attract 
little media attention the socialist premier took the 
unprecedented step of disclosing his relationship with the tall 
blonde ms liani 
opinion is divided about the possible effects on his 
governments popularity 
a parliamentarian with papandreous governing panhellenic 
socialist movement who spoke on condition of anonymity said my 
constituents are farmers with oldfashioned views about family 
life and ill have a hard time explaining this the planned 
divorce away 
but political analysts point out that previous disclosures about 
papandreous private life failed to affect his approval rating 
the analysts say the premiers refusal to appoint a standin 
during his hospitalization in england is much more likely to erode 
support for his party 
papandreou has a history of womanizing that never dented his 
political appeal but his absence leaves a power vacuum that makes 
it clear pasok is unlikely to survive unless he makes a miraculous 
recovery said stratis stratigis a lawmaker with the liberal 
opposition democratic renewal party 
during seven years in power papandreou has skillfully 
stagemanaged abrupt changes in economic and foreign policy without 
endangering his governments popularity but his panhellenic 
socialist movement now faces the prospect of fighting national 
elections due by mid1989 with a weakened leader 
papandreou flew to london on august 25 for treatment of a 
narrowing of the aorta the main blood vessel carrying blood from 
the heart 
the premiers planned surgery at harefield hospital to replace a 
heart valve has been postponed several times because of a liver 
problem 
the operation now is expected to take place in late september at 
the earliest according to his doctors 
in the meantime papandreou is advising the government by 
telephone and senior cabinet ministers take turns flying to london 
for instructions 
mrs papandreou 65 who runs a socialist feminist organization 
in greece has not visited her husband in the hospital 
she has not made any public statement on the divorce and said 
in a letter to an englishlanguage athens newspaper over the past 
weekend i will not do so until the health of andreas is 
assured 
the couple married in a civil ceremony in the united states in 
1951 when papandreou was an economics professor at the university 
of minnesota both had recently divorced 
when papandreous relationship with ms liani became public 
knowledge a year ago mrs papandreou said she did not intend to 
seek a divorce 
ms liani who studied at the sorbonne university in paris and 
works for olympic airways the greek state carrier met the premier 
through his wife in 1986 and later was assigned to his official 
plane 
at that time mrs papandreou was seeking better media promotion 
for feminism in greece and chose ms liani to host a greek 
television talk show on sexual equality called misomiso half 
and half the premier was one of the first guests interviewed by 
ms liani 
ms liani is divorcing her husband alexis kapopoulos 48 an 
architect who works for staterun television 
the papandreous have four children and two grandchildren their 
marriage has weathered difficulties in the past but this time the 
premiers attitude has markedly changed as greek commentators 
pointed out 
in the past when a serious love affair produced his 
papandreous child the issue of his marriage never surfaced 
helen vlachos wrote sunday in her column in the athens daily 
kathimerini 
but he seems to have lost a sense of reality he acts as 
though hes overlooked one detail that he is the premier of 
greece she wrote 
she was referring to papandreous illegitimate daughter born 
after an affair he had with a swedish actress while his family was 
exiled in stockholm during the 196774 military dictatorship that 
ruled greece 
that affair was revealed a few days before a general election in 
june 1985 in which papandreou was reelected by a comfortable 
majority 
papandreous meeting with his 18yearold daughter emilia nyblom 
at the end of an official visit to sweden in january was widely 
reported in greek newspapers but opinion polls showed no related 
decline in his popularity 
according to political pollster panayote dimitras the lack of 
electoral reaction is due to the fact that to many greeks 
papandreou and the other politicians are like hollywood actors so 
you dont expect them to be perfect and you certainly dont judge 
them by your own domestic standards 
</TEXT>
