<TEXT>
argentinas dante captuo the new general 
assembly president wasted no time in telling the 159nation body 
it must close the economic gulf between rich and poor nations 
as the argentine foreign minister took the gavel after his 
election tuesday he noted the remarkable difference between all 
the progress made toward ensuring world peace and the little or 
nothing we have done to prevent the widening of the gap between 
rich countries and a large part of the developing world 
caputo a 47yearold former political science professor 
defeated the only other candidate for the presidency of the 
159member general assembly barbados un ambassador dame nita 
barrow by 9166 with one abstention during a single secret ballot 
the election the first order of business in the assemblys 43rd 
session was portrayed as a showdown between britain which backed 
mrs barrow and argentina its defeated foe in the 1982 falklands 
war 
caputo won the presidency with strong support from the soviet 
bloc the developing world japan and the nonaligned movement 
including india and pakistan said diplomats and observers 
dame nita also was backed by the caribbean nations and numerous 
commonwealth countries the united states was believed to have 
voted for her said observers 
although the presidency is largely ceremonial it has the power 
to set the tone of debate caputo took advantage of that provision 
in his opening speech in which he said the world body has been 
remiss in redressing economic imbalances 
one of the clearest examples of this impotence is probably the 
question of the external foreign debt of the developing 
countries he said 
these very high interest rates together with the pitiless 
system of successive refinancing plans and the perverse outflow of 
financial resources of the indebted countries to the creditors 
will end up eliminating the possibilities of investment for the 
developing world he said 
caputo helped bring argentina out of the international isolation 
it suffered under a series of military juntas from 19761983 and 
his speech reflected his alliance with the developing world 
as assembly president caputo can cut short speeches and arrange 
their order and has important informal powers to set up backstage 
meetings and compromises among delegateshe replaces outgoing 
president peter florin of east germany 
in his speech caputo cited recent un strides in addressing 
regional conflicts including the iraniraq truce the afghan 
accords a settlement in the western sahara and promoting dialogue 
between cypriot factions and warring cambodian parties 
but he added the situation in central america appears as a 
particularly painful contrast within the pattern of evolution of 
regional conflicts 
he also hailed the ussoviet arms agreement to destroy all 
intermediate nuclear missiles and called for the implementation of 
un resolutions that would grant a palestinian homeland and 
guarantee israels right to exist in peace with its arab neighbors 
he singled out south africas infamous practice of apartheid 
as an intransigent problem that constitutes a true affront to the 
moral conscience of mankind 
for the second year in a row secretarygeneral javier perez de 
cuellar missed the sessions start he left tuesday for a trip to 
south africa his first in five years for talks on a regional 
peace settlement last year he was holding talks on ending the 
iraniraq war 
the assembly begins its threeweek general debate on monday when 
president reagan addresses the body 
