<TEXT>
the new general assembly president 
foreign minister dante caputo of argentina has a reputation as a 
canny and ambitious diplomat with empathy for the third world 
the useducated envoy has become known for bringing argentina 
back into world diplomacy and out of its pariah status under 
military juntas that ruled from 197683 
caputo 47 is a former professor of political science who was 
virtually unknown before president raul alfonsin elected in 
october 1983 named him foreign minister he had supported alfonsin 
in a magazine he edited until 1983 
as alfonsin promoted democracy and human rights at home caputo 
promoted argentinas image as a liberal independent activist 
latin american nation 
alfonsin and caputo resolved a centuryold dispute with chile 
over the beagle channel in 1985 six years earlier the neighboring 
countries almost went to war over the three uninhabited islands in 
the south atlantic 
argentina has cut its military spending deeply it joined one 
group that demands international nuclear disarmament and a second 
group that is promoting a peaceful political solution to the wars 
in central america 
under caputo argentina has become active in the nonaligned 
movement denouncing apartheid in south africa criticizing britain 
for staying in northern ireland and supporting palestinians in 
their quest for a homeland 
argentina broke diplomatic relations with south africa in 1986 
in his own country caputo inspires strong reactions 
university students the opposition peronist party and leftist 
elements in his own radical civic union party enthusiastically 
support him the right despises him seeng him as an opportunist 
using the general assembly presidency as a stepping stone to 
argentinas presidency 
caputo offered himself as a presidential candidate for the 
radical civic union in 1983 but alfonsin won the nomination 
caputo has shown himself to be a shrewd survivor in domestic 
politics he is the only remaining member of alfonsins original 
cabinet 
he speaks french english and spanish and studied international 
relations at harvard and tufts in the boston area where he met his 
frenchborn wife 
caputo earned a degree in political science from the university 
of el salvador in buenos aires and a doctorate in that field at the 
university of paris 
