to approve 17 articles of impeachment on aug 3 the case then went 
to the senate for trial where conviction by a twothirds majority 
would remove hastings from his lifetime job that now pays 
89500ayear 
the main impeachment article accuses hastings of conspiring with 
washington attorney william borders in 1981 to obtain a 150000 
payment from two convicted racketeers in exchange for lenient 
sentencing and return of forfeited assets 
the rules panel said there are numerous impeachment cases in 
which congress carried over proceedings from one congress to the 
next most involving cases in which the house continued its 
inquiries from congress to congress the rules committee said 
in two cases senate proceedings were continued from one 
congress to the next 
the full senate sat as an impeachment jury and as judges for all 
impeachment cases until the trial of former us district judge 
harry e claiborne in 1986 
in claibornes case a 12member committee heard testimony for 
seven days in september 1986 before the full senate convened as a 
jury in october and convicted the thenlas vegas nev judge 
hastings is the first us government official to face 
impeachment after winning acquittal in a criminal trial based on 
the same charges he also is the first black to go through the 
impeachment process in which congress determines whether an 
official should be removed from office 
hastings lawyer terence j anderson has filed legal papers 
that agree with the committees recommendation to hold the 
proceedings next year 
the rules committee also recommended that house managers of the 
case who function as prosecutors and hastings be prepared to 
proceed with witnesses by march 1 
</TEXT>
