americans average weekly earnings fell a percipitous 13 percent 
in august the decline in workers buying power was the third in 
the past four months and the worst ever on record since the 
government began keeping tabs on real earnings in 1964 
the decrease stemmed from a 09 percent drop in the average 
number of hours worked from 349 hours to 346 hours and the 04 
percent hike in consumer prices average hourly earnings were 
924 unchanged from july 
another commerce department report showed housing construction 
falling 33 percent last month with a steep drop in new 
