gain in july they have jumped a total of 106 percent over the 
last year cereal and bakery product prices were up 16 percent 
the largest monthly increase since january 1981 reflecting higher 
prices for wheat oats and eggs the government said 
excluding food there were wide price swings in both directions 
the 3 percent increase in gasoline prices for example was 
partially offset price declines of 12 percent for natural gas 08 
percent for home heating oil and 02 percent for electricity 
