one were to look at it as a manifestation of some broader changes 
if it is to be only a personnel shakeup then we are not 
interested 
deputy mikolaj kozakiewicz told parliament on monday that the 
government cannot be held responsible for polands problems because 
it lacks freedom of action he cited the dominance of the party 
apparatus over daytoday government affairs 
i am only stating aloud what everybody has known for some 
time that under the present political system the government has 
not been and is not sovereign kozakiewicz a reformminded 
member of the communistallied peasant party said 
it is impossible to institute radical economic and 
