<TEXT>
trevor pinnocks debut as an operatic conductor 
at the metropolitan opera has already raised eyebrows but the 
british early music specialist says youve got to start 
somewhere why not here 
pinnock will conduct handels giulio cesare which premieres 
tuesday with kathleen battle as cleopatra and tatiana troyanos as 
caesar jeffrey gall in the role of ptolemy is the first 
countertenor male alto to appear at the met 
the more significant first for the met is having an early music 
specialist in the pit pinnock who founded and directs the english 
concert is one of britains bestknown workers in the original 
instruments field along with christopher hogwood and john eliot 
gardner 
however the announcement that pinnock would conduct giulio 
cesare provoked some critical grousing last season donal 
henahan chief music critic of the new york times ended a 
laudatory review of one of pinnocks performances with this warning 
shot followers of the metropolitan opera must wonder what 
qualifies mr pinnock to conduct next seasons julius caesar 
the trouble is people are always ready to pigeonhole 
everybody pinnock said before rehearsal recently 
ive done giulio cesare ive done it with students on stage 
in london but the fact is ive never conducted in an opera house 
before he said 
i do know the music through and through i love the music of 
handel and i love working with singers in a certain way all 
music is sung i hate music that doesnt breathe 
pinnock 41 has been performing professionally since 1966 and 
he formed the english concert in 1973 
the met has only been doing handel since 1983 when rinaldo 
entered the repertory followed by an operatic version of the 
oratorio samson in 1985 
this production of giulio cesare was done by john copley for 
the english national opera in 1978 with charles mackerras 
conducting 
pinnock is not working with original instruments at the met but 
with a small orchestra 18 violins six cellos three basses and 
harpsichord of modern instruments 
the early music influence will come in the style of playing 
especially the ornamentation in both the instrumental and vocal 
parts 
of course it has been paramount in my musical considerations 
the combination of what handel wants and how to fill the hall 
pinnock said 
its interesting how much thats affected ornamentation i 
have quite strong ideas about the type of ornamentation that is 
suitable for a large space as opposed to a small room i think the 
ornamentation in general needs more space it cant be tight and 
fast ornamentation 
it also has to suit the voice 
ive found that ive had to write quite different 
ornamentation in some cases for cover singers pinnock said 
because obviously one is trying to solve two things in 
ornamentation first and foremost for me ones trying to enhance 
the meaning of the words and the whole sense of the aria if the 
ornamentation doesnt do that its completely wasted notes 
secondly it is to show off the voice and it must be to show off 
the beautiful qualities of whoever is singing it 
giulio cesare premiered in london in 1724 and was revised 
and revived in 1725 1730 and 1732 following its last german 
performances in 1733 it disappeared from the repertory until the 
1920s 
restoring the reputation of handels more than three dozen 
operas has become a cause for his partisans winton dean and john 
merrill knapp in a monumental scholarly survey of handels operas 
published last year contended that handel ranks with monteverdi 
mozart and verdi among the supreme masters of opera 
pinnock said handels operas have unfairly gained a reputation 
for being static that has something to do with the limitations of 
the opera seria form of recitatives mixed with da capo 
arias solos which have two movements repeating the first 
pinnock sees giulio cesare as a series of pictures in which 
the audience is invited to take part 
the da capo aria musically enhances the meaning of the 
words he said so what weve begun to understand in the 
beginning weve entered the picture then were fully in 
accordance with whats being sung and can relish the atmosphere 
before moving on to the next picture 
now of course it is possible in a certain production to make 
it so static that we as the audience are not invited in but i 
believe that the good production of a handel opera will at the same 
time honor that concept of the picture and not destroy it by 
ridiculous movement 
among pinnocks future projects is next seasons launching of 
the classical band in new york an original instruments 
orchestra of 40 or 50 players which will have guest conductors 
leonard bernstein wants to have a go pinnock said though 
thats not yet definite 
he says he wants to be free to perform any kind of music though 
pinnock admits some limitations 
im not good enough at playing jazz which upsets me a lot 
becaust cards he said 
naming the various cards he used the picture cost 100000 and 
i put 40000 on credit cards it earned 8 million at the box 
office 
hollywood shuffle is a satire on the way movie industry 
treats blacks and the compromises they face if they want to be a 
part of it hollywood shuffle got townsend some serious 
attention from the studios which suggests the most important 
color in hollywood is green 
he recently completed finding maubee a suspense story in 
which he costars with denzel washington next hell do the five 
heartbeats a comedydrama about a black singing group he wrote 
the script with his partner keenen wayans who also worked with 
him on hollywood shuffle 
now why does he wear the hat and coat when he performs comedy 
he smiled and said its just good luck ive had it for six 
years its always brought me luck 
