compared with 1185 in july and 1144 in august 1987 that means a 
hypothetical selection of goods costing 100 in 198284 would have 
cost 119 last month 
for the first eight months of 1988 retail prices were up at an 
annual rate of 46 percent compared to a 44 percent gain for all 
