<TEXT>
northrop corp on wednesday announced it had 
adopted a poison pill defense against hostile takeover 
attempts although it is not aware of any potential suitors 
in the event of a hostile takeover move the plan would allow 
northrop shareholders to buy additional northrop stock or stock in 
the potential buyer at a 50 percent discount 
such plans in common use for several years are called poison 
pills because they dilute the value of a potential buyers 
holdings thus making the target company harder to swallow 
the board noted that the action was not taken in response to 
any acquisition attempt and the board is not aware of any effort 
to acquire control of northrop according to a news release by 
the aerospace and electronics company 
rather the board considered such a plan prudent because of a 
spate of corporate takeovers in recent years the company said 
</TEXT>
