<TEXT>
here is a brief chronology of major business and 
legal actions involving the hunt brothers 
april 1980 a 12 billion loan is secured by nelson bunker 
william herbert and lamar hunt to cover margin calls from silver 
purchases the loan is secured by domestic oil and gas reserves of 
the hunts placid oil co 
august 1983 six trusts of hl hunt who died in 1974 are 
separated into individual entities for the three brothers and 
hassie margaret and caroline hunt 
march 1985 two hunt companies hunt international resources 
co and great western sugar co file for bankruptcy 
reorganization in dallas the companies list debts of more than 
237 million 
july 1986 the hunt brothers file suits against 23 banks that 
had lent them 15 billion charging them with attempting to take 
over the offshore oil industry and requesting 138 billion in 
damages 
august 1986 bankruptcy is filed for placid oil co and 
william herbert hunts personal trust and interest ownership in 
thanksgiving tower in downtown dallas 
december 1987 nelson bunker and lamar hunt file bankruptcy for 
their personal trusts and interest in thanksgiving tower 
july 1988 after months of negotiations placid oil files joint 
debt reoganization plans with bank lenders on a 10year plan to 
settle its debts and settle related litigation 
august 1988 a federal jury in new york rules the hunt brothers 
must pay more than 130 million in damages to the peruvian 
governments mineral marketing company minpeco sa for conspiring 
to corner the world silver market in the late 1970s 
september 1988 a federal judge in dallas approves the 
reorganization plan to settle 750 million in loans and lift the 
brothers trust funds out of chapter 11 bankruptcy 
september 1988 william herbert and nelson bunker hunt file for 
personal bankruptcy protection to prevent minpeco from foreclosing 
on their assets before they can appeal the verdict in the silver 
trial 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

